text: San Nicolas or San Nicolás may refer to: == Person == * Spanish name for Saint Nicholas, also called San Nicolás de Myra, San Nicolás de Bari, Nikolaos of Myra ==Places== === Aruba === * San Nicolaas === Argentina === * San Nicolás de los Arroyos, in the province of Buenos Aires ** San Nicolás Agreement, signed there * San Nicolás, Buenos Aires, in the city of Buenos Aires * San Nicolás Partido (province of Buenos Aires) === Chile === * San Nicolás, Chile, a village and comuna in Ñuble Province, Bío-Bío Region === Costa Rica === * San Nicolás District, Cartago; see districts of Costa Rica === Cuba === * San Nicolás de Bari, province of Mayabeque === Honduras === * San Nicolás, Copán * San Nicolás, Santa Bárbara === Mexico === * San Nicolás de Carretas (Chihuahua) * San Nicolás de los Garza (Nuevo León) * San Nicolás Hidalgo (Oaxaca) * San Nicolás Tolentino (San Luis Potosí) * San Nicolás, Baja California * San Nicolás, Jalisco * San Nicolás, Oaxaca * San Nicolás, Puebla * San Nicolás, Tamaulipas === Nicaragua === * San Nicolás, Estelí === Philippines === * San Nicolas, Batangas * San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte * San Nicolas, Manila * San Nicolas, Pangasinan === Peru === * San Nicolás District, Rodríguez de Mendoza (Amazonas) * San Nicolás District, Carlos Fermín Fitzcarrald (Ancash) === Spain === * San Nicolás (Pamplona) * San Nicolás del Puerto (Andalusia) * La Aldea de San Nicolás (Canaries) === United States === * San Nicolas Island, one of California's Channel Islands == Ships == *HMS San Nicolas, Royal Navy ship, formerly Spanish navy ship San Nicolás, captured at the Battle of Cape St Vincent in 1797 *SS San Nicolas, Panamanian cargo ship in service 1949-64, formerly German ship SS Claus Rickmers
title: San Nicolas
